JavaScript IntelliSense parser no longer seems to recognize class syntax when written inside of an IIFE.

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Define a class using this syntax

```
var MyClass = (function () {
  function MyClass() {
      this.id = 0;
  }
  return MyClass;
}());
```
1. Trigger IntelliSense for new MyClass(). -- nothing is shown
2. Remove IIFE and return statement

```
function MyClass() {
  this.id = 0;
}
```
1. Trigger IntelliSense for new MyClass(). -- IntelliSense is provided again

In the previous version of VS Code this format was supported and provide auto-complete options for the class as expected. I ended up going with this syntax because that is what I saw TypeScript converting class syntax down to.  However, as of the latest patch I no longer get IntelliSense on any of these classes unless I remove the IIFE and return statement.
Was this an intentional change?  Is there any official documentation on what types of class syntax VS Code will support for auto-completion?

