- VSCode Version: 1.7
- OS Version: OSX

We are highlighting the output from our extension by creating a language + grammar and associating it with `text/x-code-output` mimetype:

```
  "contributes": {
    ...
    "languages": [
      {
        "id": "wallaby-output",
        "mimetypes": [
          "text/x-code-output"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "grammars": [
      {
        "language": "wallaby-output",
        "scopeName": "wallaby.output",
        "path": "./wallaby-output.tmLanguage"
      }
    ]
  },
```

![screen shot 2016-08-26 at 6 31 37 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/979966/17999152/5feb3a20-6bbb-11e6-8e69-9dc2e5633170.png)

In 1.7 our extension's output highlighting is broken because `mimetypes` were removed, so now it's not possible anymore to apply some language to an output channel. Until [there's the proper solution](https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/issues/11005) via API, is there any workaround to fix the highlighting for output channels?

